The paper deals with face recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model is a deep learning architecture, which suggests that it could also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions a new dataset, which could suggest multimedia (cs.MM) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed model on unconstrained face recognition, which could suggest information retrieval (cs.IR) as another possible sub-category.
